      <h2 class="detail-page__heading">
        For Clubs & Community Groups Interested in Affilliation
      </h2>

      <p class="detail-page__lead">
        Clubs, school organizations, and community groups that operate independently
        are generally unable to issue official rank certifications and may gradually
        develop their own training methods.<br>
        Some groups whose instructors transferred away or became unavailable have
        since joined Seishinkai and now operate as official branch dojos.<br>
        While Seishinkai is not primarily competition-focused, members are free to
        participate in tournaments hosted by other organizations, including both
        point sparring and full-contact events.<br>
        Many of our members previously earned ranks in other karate styles before
        joining Seishinkai.<br>
        We would be happy to discuss your situation with you.
        Please <a href="#contact">contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="detail-page__note">
        Examples include Wado-ryu, Shotokan, Goju-ryu, Shito-ryu,
        Shorinji-ryu, Kyokushin, Seido Kaikan, Ashihara Karate,
        Shorinji Kempo, and many others.
      </p>

